diff:1616291984:1616291984:=1,69d0%0a%3c (:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c [[!LanguageOfTheNacirema]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !Philosophy lessons from REST%0a%3c %0a%3c :Author: TimG%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Summary:''' \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c REST-based cultural analysis of the Nacirema %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c When one lays his head to REST, he RESTS his head on a pillow, or on the bare mattress. And when one goes on no more, we lay him down to REST in the ground, at least one RESTS his hope that possibility. But let's not REST there, we still have the REST of the way to go. One might REST his case in an argument When playing music, one takes a REST in a REST, only to play the REST of his part. And if it's a violin, he has his chin on the chin-REST the entire time, and the audience will REST their eyes upon him as he plays.%0a%3c %0a%3c From this usage of the word rest, we can see that the Nacirema culture is one of, well, rest. They find comfort in relaxation, and do all they can to remind themselves that comfort is near. Whenever something hard comes to an end, even a temporary end, they breathe a sigh of relief, for now they can "rest". Even their law takes a relaxed air, and their sports the same. Their entire culture is permeated by this break-taking belief.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Na